-- ArcelorMittal to Invest $11 Million in Romanian Plant
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2013-01-11T09:31:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-11/arcelormittal-to-invest-11-million-in-romanian-plant.html
A Romanian unit of  ArcelorMittal (MT) 
plans to invest about 8.5 million euros ($11 million) this year
to increase work safety at its steel plant in the eastern city
of Galati.  ArcelorMittal Galati plans to eliminate work-related
accidents through the investment program, the company said in an
e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
